<TITLE> Committees formed on powdered milk sale </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 29 (bdnews24.com)  The government has formed committees in the districts to review sale and marketing of powdered and liquid milk and milk-based products, the health ministry says.. The ministry in a press release on Wednesday said each of five-strong monitoring committees will be headed by the deputy commissioner (DC) with the civil surgeon being the secretary. In the wake of melamine contents found in milk powder, the ministry formed the committees Tuesday, it said. Other members of the committee are superintendent of police, district information officer and a representative of the municipality mayor. The committees have been tasked to ensure that proper standards are maintained while marketing milk and milk-based products. Meanwhile, the ministry in another press statement released on Wednesday said the government had been reviewing the Breast Milk Substitute (Market Regulation) Act, 1984 in a bid to make it up to date. bd
